This paper deals with the structure and connectivity of the global Internet, which falls under the category of computer networks (cs.NI). The paper also discusses validation techniques for the inferred relationships, which could fall under the category of security and privacy (cs.CR) or social and information networks (cs.SI). Additionally, the paper discusses the limitations of present measuring techniques, which could fall under the category of distributed, parallel, and cluster computing (cs.DC) or information theory (cs.IT).
